## 🔑 Central Gustatory Pathway

### Pathway from Tongue to Cortex

| Level | Structure | Notes |
|-------|-----------|-------|
| **1st neuron** | TRC → afferent fiber (CN VII, IX, X) → ganglion | Chorda tympani, petrosal, nodose ganglia |
| **2nd neuron** | Ganglia → **Nucleus Tractus Solitarius (NTS)**, rostral gustatory nucleus, medulla | Ipsilateral relay; CN VII → most rostral; CN X → most caudal; tonotopy of NTS by taste quality and receptor field |
| **3rd neuron** | NTS → **Central tegmental tract (CTT)** → **Ventral posteromedial nucleus of thalamus (VPM)**, parvocellular medial portion | Distinct from VPL (somatic body) and from somatosensory face representation; taste VPM is medial to face VPM |
| **4th neuron** | VPM → **Primary gustatory cortex**: **anterior insula** and **frontal operculum** (Brodmann areas 43/13 anterior) | Conscious taste perception; quality discrimination |
| **Further processing** | Primary cortex → **Orbitofrontal cortex (OFC)** | **Secondary gustatory cortex**: integration of taste + retronasal smell + texture + temperature → **flavor perception**; also reward value of food |

### Limbic and Hypothalamic Projections (from NTS and Higher Centers)

| Target | Function |
|--------|---------|
| **Amygdala** | Taste aversion (conditioned food aversion — powerful single-trial learning); disgust responses; reward/punishment valuation of food |
| **Hypothalamus (lateral)** | Feeding drive; palatability signals |
| **Striatum (nucleus accumbens)** | Reward; palatability-driven eating beyond caloric need; dopamine release during palatable food intake |
| **Parabrachial nucleus (pons)** | Relay to amygdala and hypothalamus for taste-driven reflexes (vomiting, salivation) |

